questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a distributed saga orchestrator calls a local service wrapped in a Spring `@Transactional` boundary. When a custom `OrderValidationException` (which extends the checked `Exception` class) is thrown due to a validation failure, database writes made during the transaction are NOT rolling back, causing data inconsistency across downstream microservices.

Here is the target service code:

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Transactional
    public void processOrder(OrderDto order) throws OrderValidationException {
        saveOrderDetails(order);
        if (isInvalid(order)) {
            throw new OrderValidationException("Validation failed");
        }
    }
}
